Day 13: Yoga with Adriene - Endurance & Ease. I had a few days now where I was unable to give myself the time and come and bring myself to the mat. Thats ok, because here I am on day thirteen and it's an auspicious kind of day. My return highlights, to myself, my dedication to my self improvement both physically and mentally. I know the spirit of the challenge is that we follow along 30 days in a row. Kudos to those that do. But also know that life happens sometimes and we can always make up a day or two. Persistence, determination, and having your heart in what you do will see you through this challenge, and any other dreams you aim to achieve. It felt good to move again after missing the past couple of days. Thank you for a wonderful session Adriene! Namaste.

I've been a competitive runner since age 12, and I could never even touch my toes. ¬†Throughout the past year, I've ran more miles than seconds I spent stretching. ¬†A stress fracture forced me to stop running for 6 weeks. ¬†Instead of letting the injury be devastating, I decided to use it to improve my running by focusing on stretching and strengthening. ¬†I am so happy it brought me to your site! ¬†The first few days were extremely difficult. ¬†As a runner, your mind must be engaged the entire time, pushing your body to go faster, farther. ¬†It has taken practice to "check out" with my mind and focus on breathing. ¬†Even as a beginner (beginner is an understatement), I come out of your sessions feeling confident and ready for more, which is more than I can say for any other yoga class I've been to. ¬†One day soon maybe I'll even be able to touch my toes thanks to you :) ¬†Thank you for doing this!!
